  "text": "The OpenJDK HotSpot JVM JIT compilation pipeline is composed of several key components found in the src/hotspot/share/ directory. CompileBroker (compiler/compileBroker.hpp) is the central broker that manages all compilation requests and maintains the compilation queue. CompilerThread (compiler/compilerThread.hpp) defines the dedicated threads that execute compilation tasks. The two-tiered compilation system consists of AbstractCompiler (compiler/abstractCompiler.hpp), which is the base class providing the common interface for all compilers. The C1 compiler (c1/c1_Compiler.hpp) provides first-tier just-in-time compilation for fast startup and initial method compilation, implementing the Compiler class derived from AbstractCompiler. The C2 compiler (opto/c2compiler.hpp) provides second-tier optimizing compilation, implementing the C2Compiler class for highly-optimized native code generation. This tiered architecture allows the JVM to balance between quick startup (C1) and peak performance (C2)."
}

